WEBVTT

00:01.558 --> 00:03.874
<i>Mystic Falls...
I was born here.</i>

00:04.564 --> 00:06.190
<i>This is my home.</i>

00:06.323 --> 00:08.381
<i>- And mine.
- And mine.</i>

00:08.926 --> 00:11.932
<i>For centuries, supernatural
creatures have lived among us.</i>

00:12.060 --> 00:14.701
<i>They were vampires,
werewolves, doppelgangers...</i>

00:14.840 --> 00:16.803
<i>- witches.
- And even hybrids.</i>

00:16.832 --> 00:18.788
- There are those who protect them...
- What's going on?

00:18.914 --> 00:20.754
We just need to ask you a
few questions about your son.

00:20.783 --> 00:22.734
You have no idea
what you're up against.

00:22.763 --> 00:24.361
<i>And those who want them dead.</i>

00:24.390 --> 00:26.045
We are the beginning.

00:28.626 --> 00:30.728
<i>They are the ones we love.</i>

00:32.164 --> 00:33.957
<i>And the ones we've lost.</i>

00:33.987 --> 00:35.805
This magic is dark.

00:36.424 --> 00:39.573
You made your choice. Now
they're taking it out on me.

00:39.774 --> 00:42.362
- I'm sorry, grams! No!
- No!

00:43.039 --> 00:45.774
<i>Then there's Elena.
She's one of us now.</i>

00:46.168 --> 00:47.771
<i>A vampire.</i>

00:48.713 --> 00:50.630
<i>And I'll do anything
to help her survive.</i>

00:51.424 --> 00:54.179
Sincro: addic7ed.com
Resincronizado por Siena

01:09.801 --> 01:11.507
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:11.537 --> 01:13.465
- You're making a big mistake.
- No, I'm not.

01:13.495 --> 01:15.938
If I can get Elena used to
animal blood right out the gate...

01:16.198 --> 01:18.759
- You're reaching.
- ... Maybe she'll be able to bypass

01:18.789 --> 01:21.361
- all the things that we went through.
- Delusional.

01:21.489 --> 01:23.746
- Maybe she actually has a shot at this.
- Wrong.

01:23.777 --> 01:26.215
- You're just wrong, Stefan.
- She won't be able to handle it

01:26.245 --> 01:29.474
if she hurts someone, Damon.
Her compassion is her Achilles' heel,

01:29.504 --> 01:31.335
and everything is
magnified right now.

01:31.365 --> 01:33.081
Then you better hope
she's not a fan of Bambi.

01:38.540 --> 01:40.194
Close your eyes.

01:47.304 --> 01:49.972
She needs human blood,
Stefan. From the vein.

01:50.100 --> 01:52.882
Oh, come on, you know what happens.
You name me a vampire

01:52.912 --> 01:54.896
who didn't kill at least one
person when they were new.

01:54.926 --> 01:57.704
You name me one who went on the
bunny diet and didn't kill dozens.

02:01.570 --> 02:03.566
If she kills someone,
she will crumble.

02:03.596 --> 02:07.012
How much pain do you think she can take
before she shuts off her humanity switch?

02:07.129 --> 02:09.521
It happens to the best
of us at least once.

02:09.787 --> 02:12.064
We get over it, Stefan.
A hundred years or so.

02:12.094 --> 02:13.913
Yeah, well, I think I'd
like her to skip that part.

02:14.193 --> 02:16.402
She can't learn
to control the blood lust

02:16.432 --> 02:18.669
if she's never actually
experienced the blood lust.

02:18.798 --> 02:20.588
- What are you doing? Knock it off.
- It's like a cheat.

02:20.618 --> 02:22.798
Like giving a kid a calculator
before they know math.

02:23.057 --> 02:24.858
I said stop.

02:29.370 --> 02:30.931
Don't worry, he'll heel.

02:30.961 --> 02:32.682
Bigger animals
are more resilient.

02:33.302 --> 02:34.305
Hey.

02:34.728 --> 02:36.504
You did it.

02:36.862 --> 02:38.287
I know it's hard.

02:40.170 --> 02:41.937
But you can do this.

02:46.667 --> 02:49.115
Wow.
What's going on?

02:49.376 --> 02:52.828
Oh, we're just having a little
disagreement about process, right?

02:52.966 --> 02:54.646
You're still not on board
with the animal plan.

02:54.798 --> 02:55.733
Nope.

02:55.763 --> 02:58.534
I say rip off the proverbial
band-aid and let it bleed.

02:58.564 --> 03:00.875
You're a vampire, Elena.
Be a vampire.

03:01.341 --> 03:03.162
You ready to go?

03:05.500 --> 03:07.390
Vampires eat people.

03:07.840 --> 03:09.634
It's part of the natural
food pyramid.

03:11.490 --> 03:12.973
Trust me.

03:13.233 --> 03:15.182
You're going to be miserable.

03:16.009 --> 03:17.514
- I can't do it.
- All right,

03:17.544 --> 03:19.235
it's like the starting
line of a race, right?

03:19.264 --> 03:21.746
So you just push off with every
ounce of strength that you have, ok?

03:21.776 --> 03:23.889
I was a cheerleader.
I sucked at track.

03:23.919 --> 03:26.193
Just concentrate, ok?
You can do it.

03:28.134 --> 03:31.537
I can't. All I can think about
is your hands on my body.

03:32.158 --> 03:35.150
No, no, no, I didn't...
I didn't say take them off.

03:35.546 --> 03:37.378
- It feels good.
- Yeah?

03:39.411 --> 03:41.152
What does it feel like?

03:43.182 --> 03:45.180
It feels like you're touching every...

03:45.597 --> 03:47.461
nerve on my body.

03:49.521 --> 03:51.281
Everything is heightened.

03:52.894 --> 03:54.240
Taste.

03:55.251 --> 03:56.939
The smell.

03:57.860 --> 04:00.397
Sight. Touch.

